<p>Storm track map layer, current weather forecasts, and Nest or Honeywell compatibility make it more than a simple weather app. You&#8217;ll reach for this app &#8220;just because.&#8221; Nice and convenient.</p>
</div><div class="one_third last">
<figure id="attachment_53647" style="width: 203px;" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Weather-Underground-Android-Apps-e1454342593951.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-53647" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Weather-Underground-Android-Apps-e1454342593951.jpg" alt="Weather Underground Android Apps" width="203" height="360" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Weather Underground Android Apps</figcaption></figure>
<p><strong> <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.wunderground.android.weather" target="_blank">Weath</a></strong><strong><a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.wunderground.android.weather" target="_blank">er Underground</a> </strong></p>
<p>Broken down by the hour, this app provides an &#8220;intensity&#8221; level as well time of rainfall. That way, I know whether or not I should grab the emergency umbrella out of the back of my car.</p>
</div><div class="clear"></div>
