8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"indiana towns";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:9;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"jessica nunemaker";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:10;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"ripley county";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:11;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"southern indiana";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://littleindiana.com/?p=49612";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:140:"Turquoise Hen is a fabulous upscale women's lifestyle boutique featuring Annie Sloan Chalk Paint, designer dresses, jewelry, and home decor.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Jessica Nunemaker";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10261:"<figure id="attachment_53595" style="width: 600px;" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-5.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-53595" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-5.jpg" alt="Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana" width="600" height="338" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana: This is the Dresser I LOVE</figcaption></figure>
The Turquoise Hen in <a href="http://littleindiana.com/category/littletowns/batesville/" target="_blank">Batesville, Indiana</a> is an upscale women&#8217;s clothing lifestyle boutique and home decor destination that&#8217;s easy to find&#8211;and impossible to leave. There are just so <strong>many pretty things</strong> to touch, browse, and admire.</p>
<p>Some people have a way with words, or cooking, or gardening. For owner Stephanie Bamonte, she has a way with redoing vintage furniture, finding just the right items to stock in her <strong>beautiful boutique</strong>&#8211;and how to arrange it all. If you&#8217;ve been feeling a little &#8220;ho-hum.&#8221; One visit to Turquoise Hens will turn it all around. </p>
<h2><strong>Turquoise Hen in Batesville</strong></h2>
<figure id="attachment_53591" style="width: 338px;" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-3.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-53591" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-3.jpg" alt="Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana" width="338" height="600" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana Carries Designer Clothing</figcaption></figure>
Some of you intrepid, brave, and rugged Indiana explorers may have already wandered into this shop&#8217;s original location. It has since moved from the RomWeber area into a<strong> lovely, bright space</strong>.</p>
<p>A large window display area enables Stephanie to easily highlight her wares to any passersby. She has much more room all around&#8211;and such <strong>an adorable storefront</strong>.</p>
<p>I was tagging along with Ripley County Tourism pro Katherine Taul for the day. We wanted to get into the shop but we weren&#8217;t even sure where it had <strong>relocated within Batesville</strong>. We had just left another business when I realized the time&#8211;they were probably going to close soon!</p>
<p>You better believe I didn&#8217;t want to miss this one. I had a book (affiliate link&#8211;see how I use wishlists to shop small) <strong><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0253020611/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325&amp;creativeASIN=0253020611&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=littleindia0b-20&amp;linkId=VELMJZQKUYNRZEYG" rel="nofollow">Little Indiana: Small Town Destinations</a><img style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="http://ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=littleindia0b-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=0253020611" alt="" width="1" height="1" border="0" /></strong> to finish up and I wanted to make sure I could include it.</p>
<p>In separate cars as we were, <strong>we both managed to call</strong> and get in touch with the shop owner before we arrived, without knowing that that was what the other person was doing! Ah, it&#8217;s nice that Kid #1 is older now (9 at the time of our visit) and can handle things like that.</p>
<p>Anyway, I guess you could say that Stephanie of <strong>Turquoise Hen</strong> had plenty of advance notice!</p>
<h3><strong>Big on Beauty</strong></h3>
<figure id="attachment_53597" style="width: 355px;" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-53597" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana.jpg" alt="Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana" width="355" height="600" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana is Pretty on the Outside too!</figcaption></figure>
Some people think that you can only &#8220;make a go of it&#8221; if you&#8217;ve got a big city locale. <strong>Stephanie&#8217;s proving otherwise</strong>. Customers, new and regular, specifically arrive in Batesville for her shop, driving in from miles and miles around.</p>
<p>Every part of this shop is organized. It&#8217;s clean and shining, <strong>welcoming and comfortable</strong>.</p>
<p>This isn&#8217;t just a women&#8217;s clothing boutique. Stephanie terms it a<strong> women&#8217;s upscale lifestyle clothing boutique</strong>. You are just as likely to find a stylish designer dress (in a range of sizes) to wear to a big event as you are to find premium denim,  yoga clothing lines, and vintage furniture.</p>
<p>She also has <strong>One Love Organics skin care</strong> and some of the best-smelling candles ever. EVER.</p>
<h3><strong>Vintage Furniture and Chalk Paint® by Annie Sloan</strong></h3>
<figure id="attachment_53608" style="width: 600px;" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-6-e1454081730951.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-53608" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-6-e1454081730951.jpg" alt="Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana" width="600" height="338" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana Designer Clothing</figcaption></figure>
Ah, the <strong>vintage furniture</strong>. At Turquoise Hen, Stephanie doesn&#8217;t only carry <a href="http://www.anniesloan.com/" target="_blank">Chalk Paint® decorative paints by Annie Sloan</a> (as well as the waxes and brushes), she uses the paint to give old things a fresh face.</p>
<p><strong>Are you familiar with Annie Sloan paint?</strong> Well, it&#8217;s gorgeous stuff! It&#8217;s also exclusive. A shop has to be approved to carry it and no one else will be allowed to carry it within so many miles. It&#8217;s a big deal!</p>
<p>At Turquoise Hen, she carries the <strong>most beautifully redone pieces of furniture</strong>. The red dresser? Oh, I want that so much it hurts.</p>
<p>But, it was either buy a dresser or take the kids back home with me. <strong>I chose the kids</strong>. I&#8217;m sorta kinda attached to them.</p>
<p>Kidding aside, each of the <strong>lovely painted pieces</strong> in Stephanie&#8217;s shop are ready for a new home. Will it be yours?</p>
<h3><strong>Inside Turquoise Hen</strong></h3>
<figure id="attachment_53596" style="width: 338px;" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-4.jpg"><img class="wp-image-53596 size-full" src="http://littleindiana.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Turquoise-Hen-Batesville-Indiana-4-e1454082139815.jpg" alt="Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana: Fancy Chickens, Annie Sloan Paint, and Designer Clothing Have a Place" width="338" height="550" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Turquoise Hen in Batesville, Indiana: Fancy Chickens, Annie Sloan Paint, and Designer Clothing Have a Place</figcaption></figure>
If your furniture could use a bit of a boost, pop inside of Turquoise Hen. Not only will you find<strong> stylish items for you and your home</strong>, but you can take a class to learn how to make-over your own tired pieces.</p>
<p>Oh, if you act quickly, her next workshop,<strong> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1005871999484837/" target="_blank">Chalk Paint® 101 Workshop</a></strong>, will be Saturday, January 30 at 10 AM &#8211; 1 PM EST. There is a fee but it will cover all of the needed supplies.</p>
<p>The workshop will cover the <strong>basic techniques</strong> of painting with Chalk Paint: 2-color distressed; color washing; smooth/modern; textured/rustic.</p>
<h3><strong>Fun Things to Do in Batesville</strong></h3>
<p>Making the trip to Turquoise Hens may not change your life&#8211;but it will definitely <strong>up your style factor</strong> (and possibly show you a few new things) as you live it!</p>
<p>You can follow along in the new products, sales, and general day to day happenings on<strong> <a title="Turquoise Hen on Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/The-Turquoise-Hen-599402780124956/" target="_blank">Turquoise Hen on Facebook</a></strong>, <a title="Turquoise Hen on Twitter" href="https://twitter.com/theturquoisehen" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, and even Instagram.</p>
<p>Be sure to use the <strong>hashtag #littleindiana</strong> to show off the pretty things you&#8217;ve picked up at Turquoise Hen.</p>
