Baby, it&#8217;s cold outside. But that doesn&#8217;t mean you should wallow on the sofa, binge watching Doctor Who before Netflix removes it February 1, while shoving <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/2011/12/christmas-popcorn-recipe/" target="_blank">Christmas Popcorn</a></strong> in your mouth. There&#8217;s a better way.</p>
<p>Instead, you can head to beautiful <a href="http://littleindiana.com/tag/brown-county/" target="_blank">Brown County</a> and join in the fun of <a href="http://www.browncounty.com/winter-wellness-weekend" target="_blank"><strong>weekend retreat</strong> <strong>Winter in the Woods</strong></a>. Brown County isn&#8217;t only an autumn destination. Appreciate its beauty and small town atmosphere a different time of year.</p>
<h2><strong>Winter in the Woods</strong></h2>
<p>Anyone will find something to fit their tastes. No, really! I have a feeling that by the end of this article, you will be making <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/category/littletowns/nashville/" target="_blank">Nashville, Indiana travel plans</a></strong>.</p>
<p>On Saturday, January 15, there&#8217;s the <strong><a href="http://www.browncounty.com/calendar/event/frosty-trails-5-mile" target="_blank">Frosty Trails 5K</a></strong>, a walk or run event. Hit the trails at Brown County State Park! Sign up at the Lower Shelter. Show your parking receipt for a full refund. Admission for this event is $25 and includes a long sleeve t-shirt and post-race drinks and food. <strong><a href="https://www.signmeup.com/site/reg/register.aspx?fid=WP2VNH7" target="_blank">Sign up for the Frosty trails 5K here</a></strong>.</p>
<p>Is running not your style? How about a hike? Choose from the 3.5 Southern Loop Hike or the 2.75 mile Woodland Hike while picking up a few facts about winter woodland facts from DNR interpreters. The Boy Scouts will have s&#8217;mores ready and waiting! <strong><a href="http://www.browncounty.com/calendar/event/winter-hike" target="_blank">Read more about the Brown County Winter Hike</a></strong>.</p>
<p>If you want something a little shorter, head to the Brown County Visitors Center at 1 PM this Saturday. <strong>Take the <a href="http://www.browncounty.com/calendar/event/tea-zer-hike-2016" target="_blank">Tea-zer Hike</a></strong>, a quick-paced walk around the 1.5 mile Salt Creek Trail. After forty minutes (or so) in the brisk winter air, it&#8217;s time for tea at <a href="http://littleindiana.com/2015/10/nashville-coffee-tea-shops/" target="_blank">Sweetea&#8217;s Tea Shop</a>! There will be a Tea 201 class occurring and, for a small fee, you may learn how tea drinking can help keep you healthy this year.</p>
<p>But that&#8217;s not all. There&#8217;s also <strong><a href="http://www.browncounty.com/calendar/event/warm-up-from-within" target="_blank">Warm Up from Within</a></strong>, an energizing wellness weekend retreat.</p>
<h3><strong>Warm Up from Within</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Mind, body, and spirit</strong>. That&#8217;s the focus of Warm Up from Within.</p>
<p>This weekend retreat<strong> isn&#8217;t about restriction</strong>. There are no jam-packed itineraries to follow or checklists to mark off. Instead, you can pick and choose what appeals to you&#8211;and listen to what your body is telling you.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s about<strong> yoga, sacred dance, art, meditative movement</strong>, and so much more. As Lee Edgren, owner of <a href="http://www.riverlightyoga.com/" target="_blank">River Light Yoga</a> and host of the event, shared with the Brown County Blog, &#8220;So often, we rely too heavily on outside information to tell us how we are doing and ignore information from our own heart and spirit.&#8221;</p>
<p>She continued, &#8220;Warm Up From Within is filled with activities that encourage us to get in touch with <strong>our inner light and life</strong> and to respond more fully from our own hearts and minds.”</p>
