<h2><strong>Indiana Christmas Festivals and Events</strong></h2>
<p>Tonight is the first night for the <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/bremen-holy-walk/2015-12-18/" target="_blank">Bremen Holy Walk</a></strong>. Don&#8217;t worry if you miss it, they do it again on Saturday, too. You know where to find the details. Hint: follow the link.</p>
<p>Grab your hat, your gloves, and a warm scarf. The Big Oaks National Wildlife Refuge needs your help for the <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/big-oaks-nwr-annual-bird-count/" target="_blank">Big Oaks NWR Annual Bird Count</a></strong>. All day or half day counts&#8211;it begins at 8 AM.</p>
<p>Danville continues their <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/winterland-christmas-light-show/2015-12-18/" target="_blank">Winterland Christmas Show at Ellis Park</a></strong>. Drive through the light show extravanganza that includes a thirty foot tree and music playing through your car radio.</p>
<p>Get in to Davis Mercantile in Shipshewana to view the <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/gingerbread-house-display/2015-12-18/" target="_blank">Gingerbread House Display</a></strong>. Vote for your favorite creation. It&#8217;s an ongoing event so make sure to pencil that one in.</p>
<p>Tours for the <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/christmas-at-seiberling-mansion/2015-12-18/" target="_blank">Christmas at Seiberling Mansion</a></strong> in Kokomo continue through December 22. Time is running out. Don&#8217;t miss your chance to view this amazing mansion in all of its holiday grandeur.</p>
<p>Get in a festive mood with <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/holiday-pops/" target="_blank">Holiday Pops in Valparaiso</a></strong>. Enjoy the holiday favorites and sing-a-long at the Memorial Opera House. Discounted rates for seniors and military.</p>
<p><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/santas-great-big-led-tree-of-lights/2015-12-18/" target="_blank"><strong>Santa&#8217;s Great Big LED Tree of Lights</strong></a> is going strong in Kris Kringle Plaza. This Santa Claus, Indiana favorite will have little ones clapping with delight. It&#8217;s easy to find, too.</p>
<p>Sure, it&#8217;s a little chilly out there, but it&#8217;s also a great time to get out and see a little nature&#8211;while doing something that doesn&#8217;t involve eating Christmas cookies. Participate in the <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/winter-bird-hike/" target="_blank">Winter Bird Hike at McCloud Nature Park</a></strong> in North Salem. Guides will show you the nests of area birds. Learning is fun again.</p>
<p>December 19 marks <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/holiday-in-the-park/" target="_blank">Holiday in the Park</a></strong> at the Washington Township Park Pavilion Center in Avon.</p>
<p>Head to Danville, Indiana and the <a href="http://www.royaltheaterdanville.info/" target="_blank">Royal Theater</a> for <strong><a href="http://littleindiana.com/event/kiwanis-family-film-night-its-a-wonderful-life/" target="_blank">Kiwanis Family Film Night</a></strong> showing of It&#8217;s a Wonderful Life. It&#8217;s December 20, from 7 PM &#8211; 9 PM. Family fun on the cheap!</p>
<h3><strong>Things to Do in Indiana this Weekend</strong></h3>
<p>Is this fun or what? There&#8217;s sure to be <strong>something near you</strong>. Thanks to Little Indiana, you may find it easily. View the map below for a rough idea of where to find these scheduled activities.</p>
<p>Small Towns: Destinations, not Drive-Thrus! I&#8217;m Jessica Nunemaker and <strong>THIS</strong> is little Indiana!</p>
<p>Just don&#8217;t forget to tell &#8217;em that  <em>little Indiana</em> sent you!</p>
