			</p><div id="zlrecipe-summary" itemprop="description"><p class="summary italic">A delicious recipe for coffee cake. This comes from the "Taste of Home Baking" Cookbook. </p></div></div><p id="zlrecipe-ingredients" class="h-4 strong">Ingredients</p><ul id="zlrecipe-ingredients-list"><div id="zlrecipe-ingredient-0" class="ingredient-label" >Cake:</div><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-1" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 Cup Butter, Softened</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-2" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 Cup Sugar</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-3" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2 Eggs</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-4" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 teaspoons Vanilla Extract</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-5" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 1/2 Cups Flour</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-6" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 teaspoon Baking Soda</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-7" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 Salt</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-8" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 Cup Sour Cream</li><div id="zlrecipe-ingredient-9" class="ingredient-label" >Topping:</div><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-10" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 Cup Sugar</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-11" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 Cup Chopped Pecans</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-12" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">2 teaspoons Cinnamon</li><div id="zlrecipe-ingredient-13" class="ingredient-label" >Filling: </div><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-14" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1 Tablespoon Cornstarch</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-15" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">3/4 Cup Milk (2% or Whole)</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-16" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/4 Cup Butter, Softened</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-17" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/4 Cup Shortening</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-18" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 Cup Sugar</li><li id="zlrecipe-ingredient-19" class="ingredient" itemprop="ingredients">1/2 teaspoon Vanilla Extract</li></ul><p id="zlrecipe-instructions" class="h-4 strong">Instructions</p><ol id="zlrecipe-instructions-list" class="instructions"><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-0" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Cream Butter and Sugar in bowl of electric mixer. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-1" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Add Eggs, one at a time. Beat well. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-2" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Combine Dry Ingredients. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-3" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Add Dry Ingredients alternately with Sour Cream. Mix just until combined. Do not overmix!</li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-4" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Pour batter into two greased and wax paper-lined 9" round pans.</li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-5" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Combine Topping Ingredients. Sprinkle over batter. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-6" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Using a knife, cut through batter to swirl. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-7" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Bake 350* for 20-25 minutes or until a toothpick tester inserted near the center comes out clean. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-8" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Cool for ten minutes and then remove from pans to a wire rack. </li><div id="zlrecipe-instruction-9" class="instruction-label" >Filling:</div><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-10" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Combine Cornstarch and Milk in a small pot. Stir until smooth. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-11" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Bring to a boil, stir for a minute or two until thickened. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-12" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Cover and refrigerate until chilled. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-13" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">In a small bowl, cream thee Butter, Shortening, and Sugar until fluffy. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-14" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Add vanilla and the chilled Milk mixture. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-15" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Beat on medium speed for ten minutes until smooth. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-16" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Place one cake half on a cake plate or platter, top with filling, then top with the remaining cake. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-17" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">Store in the refrigerator. </li><li id="zlrecipe-instruction-18" class="instruction" itemprop="recipeInstructions">To serve: warm up slightly, or serve chilled, or bring a slice to room temperature. </li></ol><div class="ziplist-recipe-plugin" style="display: none;">4.4.2.1</div><a id="zl-printed-permalink" href="http://littleindiana.com/2015/12/cream-coffee-cake/" title="Permalink to Recipe">http://littleindiana.com/2015/12/cream-coffee-cake/</a></div><div id="zl-printed-copyright-statement" itemprop="copyrightHolder">Photos are the Property of little Indiana. Do Not Use Without Permission.</div></div></div>
